  "name": "Truth Serum (Ingested)",
  "type": "consumable",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>A creature subjected to this &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} must succeed on a [[/save con 11 format=long]] or become &amp;Reference[poisoned]{poisoned} for 1 hour. The &amp;Reference[poisoned]{poisoned} creature can't knowingly speak a lie, as if under the effect of a zone of truth spell.</p>\n<p><strong>Ingested.</strong> A creature must swallow an entire dose of ingested &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} to suffer its effects. The dose can be delivered in food or a liquid. You may decide that a partial dose has a reduced effect, such as allowing advantage on the saving throw or dealing only half damage on a failed save.</p>\n</div>",
